<section class="prose">
  <div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Addiction, EMDR, and Trauma Therapy in Boulder</h2>
    <h3 class="subtitle">Compassionate Mental Health Support for Recovery and Healing</h3>
    <p><strong>Welcome. I’m Scott Boyd, a Licensed Addiction Counselor, Licensed Professional Counselor and EMDR therapist in Boulder, Colorado.</strong> I help adults, professionals, and college students move through addiction, trauma, anxiety, and depression—with clarity, compassion, and lasting change.</p>
    <p>Let’s be honest—most people don’t come to therapy because life feels great. I didn’t either. I started therapy because I was in real emotional pain. If that’s where you are right now, you’re not alone. Pain hurts—but it also opens the door to transformation.</p>
    <p>You may be here because of something specific happening in your life. But real relief doesn’t just come from solving external problems—it comes from the internal work. That’s where our focus begins.</p>
    <p>I use trauma-informed therapies like EMDR, DeTUR (an EMDR protocol for addiction), IFS-Informed EMDR, and Brainspotting, along with a grounded, nondual approach that helps you shift out of survival mode and reconnect with who you really are—beneath the pain, beneath the story. I’m also trained in EFT and use that to explore relationship challenges and attachment styles.</p>
    <p>I don’t believe you need to fix or fight every part of yourself. Instead, we work together to process what’s unresolved, let go of old patterns, and rediscover the clarity, freedom, and peace already within you.</p>
  </div>
</section>

